=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-05.jpg 1707w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-05-940x1410.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-05-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-05-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-05-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-05-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1707px) 100vw, 1707px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-06.jpg\" alt=\" Inside Villa M, soft tones, natural materials, and Philippe Starck’s thoughtful design create calming, wellness-driven spaces. From restful hotel rooms to light-filled lounges and coworking areas, every detail invites comfort and connection.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-06.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-06-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-06-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-06-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-interior-design-070725-1131-06-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn the top floor, Villa M’s rooftop offers panoramic views of the Eiffel Tower and the Dôme des Invalides. Lined with fruit trees and wicker chairs, it feels like a garden in the sky. Visitors can enjoy a drink among the greenery by day or under string lights into the evening. It is a space designed for quiet moments and shared experiences.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1601\" height=\"836\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-07.jpg\" alt=\" Perched above Montparnasse, the rooftop of Villa M offers breathtaking views of Paris framed by fruit trees, wicker chairs, and glowing string lights. A garden oasis in the sky, it’s a serene spot for drinks, relaxation, and unforgettable sunsets.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-07.jpg 1601w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-07-940x491.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-07-800x418.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-07-768x401.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-07-1536x802.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1601px) 100vw, 1601px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-08.jpg\" alt=\" Perched above Montparnasse, the rooftop of Villa M offers breathtaking views of Paris framed by fruit trees, wicker chairs, and glowing string lights. A garden oasis in the sky, it’s a serene spot for drinks, relaxation, and unforgettable sunsets.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-08.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-08-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-08-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-08-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/modern-rooftop-070725-1131-08-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWith its plant-covered structure, wellness-focused interiors, and layered public programs, Villa M shows that nature and modern life can thrive together. This is not just a place to stay or work. It is a model for a healthier, more connected way of living.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr/\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by Michael Denancé, Villa M, and Yann Monel | Architectural design of Villa M: Olivier Raffaëlli \u0026amp; Guillaume Sibaud – Triptyque Architecture | Architectural Design et Art director of the spaces of the Villa M: Philippe Starck | Assistant to the Contracting Authority: SCPM Access, Guy Sanoian | Landscaping: Coloco, Pablo Giorgef | Building Company: Eiffage Construction\u003c/h6\u003e\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
